<HEADLINE> Nigeria Banks to Collect Taxes in Foreign Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria announced Thursday four
overseas correspondent banks of the Central Bank of Nigeria to
collect taxes paid to the federal government in foreign
currencies.
</P>
<P>
They are Federal Reserve Bank of New York for payments in U.S.
Dollar, the Bank of England, London (Pound Sterling), Deutsche
Bundes Bank, Frankfurt, Germany (Deutsch Mark) and the Bank of
France, Paris (French Francs).
</P>
<P>
According to the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS), the
foreign banks are to collect tax paid by offshore (non-resident)
companies, firms incorporated and registered outside Nigeria but
perform certain services in the country from which they derive
income subject to Nigerian taxation laws.
</P>
<P>
The new system was intended to promote efficiency in the tax
collection machinery, safeguard government funds and make the
payment of taxes more convenient, said FIRS Chairman Kayode
Naiyeju. 
</P>
</TEXT>
