<HEADLINE> Rally to Honor Chinese Olympians In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, august 9 (Xinhua) -- The Atlanta Olympic Games are
over, the 16 gold medals are now history, and we should all start
again, said Fu Mingxia, a gold medalist in women's platform and
springboard diving.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came at a welcoming ceremony held by the General
Office of the CPC Central Committee and General Office of the
State Council at the Great Hall of the People here today, attended
by government and party leaders and more than 1,000 people from
different walks of life.
</P>
<P>
"There are still many struggles before us, and we should keep
our eyes on the 2000 Olympic Games in Sydney," Fu added.
</P>
<P>
"All the Chinese can rest assured that we will compete hard to
win more honor for our country," she said, speaking on behalf of
all the athletes.
</P>
<P>
China's national anthem, "March of the Volunteers," which was
heard again and again at the Olympic Games in Atlanta, was heard
again today at the Great Hall of the People, as the Olympic heroes
were honored.
</P>
<P>
Yang Hanxiong, the men's weight lifting coach, said that during
the games the coaches all reached a common understanding that all
athletes should be trained to keep up their spirit of enterprise
forever.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, a member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and a State
Councillor, congratulated the athletes warmly and extended cordial
greetings on behalf of the CPC Central Committee and State Council.
</P>
<P>
Wu Shaozu, minister of the State Physical Culture and Sports
Commission, attributed the success of the Chinese Olympic
delegation to the correct leadership of the Party Central
Committee and the State Council as well as to the tremendous
support of all Chinese both in and outside the country. "The
honor belongs to our country and our people," Wu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
