<HEADLINE> Dutch Government Opposes US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The Dutch government said today
in a statement that it could not accept the increasing application
of sanctions legislation by the US in regions outside the American
territory.
</P>
<P>
It said that the US actions represented the application of
unilaterally established sanctions legislation against actions by
companies, including Dutch business, totally outside American
territory.
</P>
<P>
"The extra-territorial legislation flies in the face of
multilateral agreements which have been and are being made on
trade and investment," the statement stated.
</P>
<P>
The statement pointed out that the Netherlands had worldwide
trading and investment interests, noting that it is the seventh
largest trading nation and is sixth on the list of international
investors.
</P>
<P>
"Given the Netherlands' position as the third largest foreign
investor in the US, and that of the US as the largest
international investor in the Netherlands, the latter is
particularly vulnerable to American legislative practices such as
the present move," it said.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch government declared that it was joining other
countries in actively preparing measures at both European and
national level to enable Dutch interests and rights to be
defended.  
</P>
</TEXT>
