</P>
<P>
Other participants and officials to the games, except soccer
officials, received 100,000 Naira (about 1,170 dollars) each and
the Supporters' Club had two million Naira (about 23,400
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Head of State awarded 500,000 Naira to each of the soccer
officials. And all medalists as well as the technical adviser to
the football team, Bonfrere Jo, were conferred with the national
honor of Member Order of the Niger, the higest honor of the
country.
</P>
<P>
General Abacha also announced the promotion of Chioma Ajunwa,
a policewoman by profession, to the rank of assistant
superintendent of police, with effect from August 1, the date on
which she won the gold medal, the first ever held by Nigerian
athlete.
</P>
<P>
The head of state also announced a 1.5 million Naira (about
17,600 Dollars) cash award for Bonfrere Jo, who was not present
at the reception ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
