<HEADLINE> 233 Dead And 284 Missing in Floods In Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Floods in east China's Fujian
Province killed 233 people, and left 284 missing and about 100,000
homeless over the past two days.
</P>
<P>
Floods caused by torrential rains in 97 townships in five
counties and cities of Longyan Prefecture since August 6 also
washed away more than 70,000 houses, inundated 58,000 hectares of
farmland, and destroyed 15,000 water conservation facilities.
</P>
<P>
Traffic, telecommunications, electricity, and water supplies
have been held up in Changting County, which bore the brunt of the
flooding.
</P>
<P>
Economic losses caused by the flooding have been estimated at
more than 1.6 billion yuan (192 million US dollars) so far.
</P>
<P>
Army units and armed police stationed in Fujian have rushed to
the flooded areas to join hands with local officials and people in
rescue and disaster-relief effort. 
</P>
