manufacturing starts at the top and then moves downward, not vice
versa.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, China's development strategy for the automobile
industry should include the upper segment, Teltschik said,
suggesting that China should devote more attention to upgrading
technical knowhow.
</P>
<P>
BMW has business operations in 120 countries and regions around
the world, and sold 1.07 million cars last year, reaping a net
profit of 692 million marks. Currently, the company has sales and
service offices in Beijing, Shanghai, Qingdao, Xiamen, Dalian, and
Haikou.  
