<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Official on Preparatory Committee's Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The specific method of forming
the Selection Committee is a significant achievement of the fourth
plenary session of the Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR), a senior official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Chen Ziying, deputy secretary-general of
the Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong SAR, said that
establishing the Selection Committee is the first step in forming
the SAR government, and choosing candidates for the first chief
executive and the Provisional Legislative Conference.
</P>
<P>
Because Hong Kong people will be involved in the process of
forming the SAR government, this will be the first time for them
to truly participate in democracy, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that the specific method of establishing the Selection
Committee takes Hong Kong's long-term interests as its starting
point, and the process and the method are both open and democratic.
</P>
<P>
In this way, permanent residents of Hong Kong who are 18 or
older and who support the "one country, two systems" policy and
the Basic law, and who are willing to fulfill the obligations of
the Selection Committee can submit their names, he explained.
</P>
<P>
"This also points to another article of the Basic Law: all Hong
Kong residents shall be equal before the law," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Chen also refuted the allegation that Hong Kong will become the
same as China's interior areas after 1997, referring to the "one
country, two systems" policy. He said it proceeds from Hong Kong's
history and reality, from the interests of Hong Kong and the whole
country, and has also taken into consideration other country's
economic interests in Hong Kong, especially those of Britain.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the hope that China and Britain will increase
consultations and co-operation on the Hong Kong question and the
British Hong Kong Government will earnestly cooperate with the
Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong SAR during the final phase
of the transition period, and that the Sino-British Joint Liaison
Group will speed up settling of some matters during this period.
</P>
<P>
In referring to the question of permanent Hong Kong residents,
Chen said that this session has approved suggestions on how to
implement Clause Two of Article 24 of the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Because these suggestions relate to Hong Kong's specific
situation, they will help make Hong Kong society more stable and
reassure the public, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
