<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Press Communique on Preparatory Committee Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The fifth plenary session of the
Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) is to be held in Beijing October 4 and 5, according
to a press communique issued here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The communique says that the fourth plenary session of the
Preparatory Committee was convened here from August 9 and 10 and
heard working reports by the heads of the four panels of the
Selection Committee and approved three documents.
</P>
<P>
These were the specific methods on the formation of the
Selection Committee for the establishment of the first government
of the Hong Kong SAR; a proposal on implementing Clause Two of
Article 24 of the Basic Law for the Hong Kong SAR; and a proposal
for provisional use of regional flags and regional emblems of the
Preparatory Committee.
</P>
<P>
The method of nominating and electing members of the Selection
Committee follows the principles of democracy, openness, justice,
and reason.
</P>
<P>
Those at the meeting expressed the hope that the people of Hong
Kong will be enthusiastically involved in submitting names and
nominating members of the Selection Committee to create a good
beginning for the preparatory work of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
It points out that implementation of Clause Two of Article 24
of the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR refers to defining
principles for deciding on qualifications of permanent residents
of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
This will be closely connected to Hong Kong residents' personal
interests and preparatory work for establishing the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
The proposal has a feasible method for determining rights of
abode for Hong Kong residents after July 1, 1997, according to the
Nationality Law of the People's Republic of China and an
explanation made by the National People's Congress Standing
Committee on implementing this law in the Hong Kong SAR,
benefitting both Hong Kong society's stability and smooth
transition, the press communique says.
</P>
<P>
Those at the meeting said that regional flags and emblems of
the Hong Kong SAR are needed for celebrations for the return of
Hong Kong to the motherland before July 1, 1997 and during the
founding of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
In order to safeguard the dignity of the regional flags and
regional emblems of the Hong Kong SAR and to ensure correct use of
them, the proposal for the provisional method on how to use the
regional flags and regional emblems of the Hong Kong SAR as
approved by the meeting is necessary, the press communique says.
</P>
</TEXT>
