<HEADLINE> Jordan Beats Pakistan in Asian Cup Soccer Qualifyer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Jeryess Tadrus scored two goals to
pace Jordan to a 4-0 victory over Pakistan in an Asian Cup soccer
qualifying match here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
National football star Tadrus put the hosts 1-0 ahead when
scored his first goal on a cross-shot by teammate Badran
al-Shaqran in the 23rd minute, sending about 9,000 spectators into
jubilation.
</P>
<P>
But the popular striker failed to score again from a penalty
kick in the final minutes of the first half, when Pakistani
goalkeeper Noman Ibrahim managed to swerve the ball to a corner.
</P>
<P>
In the 54th minute, Abdullah Sheyab scored Jordan's second goal
from a long shot, and 37 minutes later, Tadrus challenged
Pakistan's defense and made it 3-0 from a kick inside the box.
</P>
<P>
Hisham Abdul-Munim wrapped up the impressive win for Jordan in
the 85th minute when he scored the fourth goal from a 30-meter
long shot.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan meets Iraq Sunday in the second match of the
qualifying round, while Jordan takes on Iraq in Tuesday's final
match.
</P>
<P>
The Group Six winner proceeds to the finals that will be held
in the United Arab Emirates in December.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh, another member of Group Six, withdrew from the
competition, citing lack of funds to finance its team. 
</P>
