<HEADLINE> SAR Government Selection Committee Formation Methods Adopted (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 10 (Xinhua) -- A document on the mothed of
forming the Selection Committee for the establishment of the first
government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
was adopted here today at the fourth plenary session of the
Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
The document states that the make-up of the Selection Committee
should reflect a broad representation. The 400 committee members
should be permanent Hong Kong residents from four sectors: the
industrial, commercial and financial sector; professionals; labor,
grass-roots, religious, and other sectors; and former political
figures, Hong Kong deputies to the National People's Congress, and
Hong Kong members of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). Each sector
will account for 100 Selection Committee members.
</P>
<P>
Members must be at least 18 years of age, meet the requirements
of permanent Hong Kong residents as stated in Article 24 of the
Basic Law, and support the "one country, two systems" principle
and the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The committee members should be willing to carry out the
committee's duties of selecting the first Chief Executive and
electing the provisional legislature as stipulated by the National
People's Congress and the Preparatory Committee, the document says.
</P>
<P>
It points out that foreigners who are permanent Hong Kong
residents, or who meet the requirements stipulated by the Basic
Law are also eligible for nomination.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960810.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SAR Government Selection Committee Formation Methods Adopted (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The document says that anyone from the first three sectors who
wants to be elected must submit his or her name to his or her
organization (except for political organizations), or sector, or
professional group. After the information is reviewed, they can be
nominated.
</P>
<P>
The nominations will be given to the Secretariat of the
Preparatory Committee and delivered to all Preparatory Committee
members.
</P>
<P>
Based on their suggestion, the chairman and vice-chairmen will
put forward a list of candidates. The ratio of candidates to seats
must be not less than 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
As for the election, it says, members of the Preparatory
Committee can vote for candidates from the first three sectors by
secret ballot, and the winners will be the ones with the most
votes.
</P>
<P>
As for those from the fourth sector, 26 Hong Kong deputies to
the National People's Congress who are permanent Hong Kong
residents, will be un-elected members of the Selection Committee.
</P>
<P>
The number of members of the Selection Committee who are former
political figures will be 40, and there will be 34 representing
Hong Kong members of the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Former political figures who intend to take part in the
Selection Committee can submit their names to an organization of
their own sector (except for political organizations), or
organizations of other sectors. They can be nominated to the
Preparatory Committee after review. They can also be nominated
jointly by five Preparatory Committee members.
</P>
<P>
The document says, however, that the number of Selection
Committee members nominated by every Preparatory Committee member
cannot exceed three. The method for submitting names of former
political figures and for electing them will be the same for that
of the first three sectors.
</P>
<P>
The method of choosing Selection Committee members from Hong
Kong members of the CPPCC National Committee will be decided by
those Hong Kong representatives themselves, the document says.
</P>
<P>
Those belonging to several sectors can submit their names in
only one sector.
</P>
<P>
The Selection Committee members will all be chosen the same
day, and the time and place for the election will be decided by
the chairman and vice-chairmen of the Preparatory Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960810.0101 </DOCNO>
