<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The level of inflation rate in
Nigeria fell to 55.4 percent in May this year, a radio report
said here today.
</P>
<P>
A top official of the Central Bank of Nigeria was quoted as
saying that the drop is attributed to some monetary policies the
Apex Bank has taken in the past few weeks.
</P>
<P>
The local currency Naira was appreciated from 81 to one U.S.
Dollar to 80 to one earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
This is part of Nigeria's inflation level which stood at 72.5
percent in last December, 69.7 percent in this January and
continued to go down to 66.7 percent in April, according to the
Central Bank statistics. 
