<HEADLINE> Japan's E. Coli Outbreak Claims One More Victim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The E. coli outbreak claimed one
more victim today, bringing up the bacteria's death toll to a
total of nine in about a month's time.
</P>
<P>
According to a Kyodo news agency report, the latest victim of
the O-157 strain of E. coli was an 80-year-old woman in Obanazawa,
Yamagata Prefecture, of northern Japan.
</P>
<P>
The outbreak, first identified in mid-July, so far has sickened
more than 9,200 people in various parts of the country and put the
government's health officials on high alert.
</P>
<P>
Starting as a food poisoning epidemic, the O-175 bacteria
outbreak was pronounced an "infectious disease" by the government
on Tuesday. 
</P>
