<HEADLINE> Egypt to Hold Mass Wedding Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 10 (Xinhua) -- A free mass wedding ceremony for
2,000 brides and grooms will be held at the Cairo Stadium here on
September 5, a local English-language newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
A large number of Egyptian young people have applied to get
married at the ceremony sponsored by the Supreme Council for Youth
and Sports (SCYS), according to Egyptian Mail, the Saturday
edition of The Egyptian Gazette.
</P>
<P>
Several firms have volunteered to contribute to this "national
project" which is intended to alleviate the economic burdens of
some young people, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The SCYS has determined certain conditions that should be met
by brides and bridegrooms to participate in the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The bridegrooms should not exceed the age of 35, the paper
said, adding that the couples should be from the low-income
classes who cannot afford a wedding ceremony and who are in need
of financial assistance.
</P>
<P>
The 1,000 couples to participate in the wedding will be
selected from the applicants by drawing lots.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that many people support the idea of mass
wedding as most bridegrooms in Egypt are over-burdened by marriage
expenses, including buying an apartment and furnishing it.
</P>
<P>
But the idea is also facing a strong opposition in this largely
conservative Moslem country.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the mother of one of the brides who had
applied to participate in the ceremony as saying that she could
not imagine her daughter being married in such a way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
