<HEADLINE> Denmark, Hong Kong and Sichuan to Build Meat Processing Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Two companies from Denmark and
Hong Kong have concluded a contract with Sichuan Province on
jointly building a meat processing plant in this China's largest
pig-raising province.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong-based New China Hong Kong Group Ltd., the Denmark
company and the Sichuan provincial government will invest 20
million US dollars in the project.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, the first phase of construction of
the plant will be finished by the end of next year. It is designed
to produce 100,000 tons of hams annually.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan now raises 78 million pigs annually, ranking first
in the country, and one third of the pigs is sold well to other
parts of the country.
</P>
