<HEADLINE> Italian Climber's Body Recovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian rescue teams had found the
body of an Italian climber who fell into a gully on an Andean peak
in the northern Peruvian state of Ancash, police said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the body of 23-year-old Italian, Lucar Lana,
was found on the Chacraraju mountain, about 6,100 meters above sea
level.
</P>
<P>
Lana's climbing partner, Stefanno Rossi, told police that Lana
fell to the gully on Wednesday while they were returning to the
town of Yungay.
</P>
<P>
Local press said that the police rescue team had also found the
remains of another climber, apparently a German who disappeared 20
years ago on the Huascaran mountain, also in Ancash. 
