<HEADLINE> Weekly Report on KLSE Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Trading on the Kuala Lumpur
Stock Exchange (KLSE) market this week was range bound despite
moderate interest from market players.
</P>
<P>
The composite Index (CI) closed higher after selective buying
of bluechips, rising 9.04 points to close at 1,105.20 from last
week's 1,096.17 while the all Main Board Emas Index added 3.25
points to 316.89 and the Industrial Index gained 11.82 points to
2,093.98.
</P>
<P>
The grand total this week was 779.253 million shares worth
7.792 billion ringgit (about 3.117 billion US dollars) down from
799.173 million shares valued at 5.514 billion ringgit (about
2.205 billion US dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
The five-day main board turnover dropped to 475.399 million
shares worth 3.250 billion ringgit (about 1.3 billion US dollars)
from last week's total of 524.026 million shares valued at 3.316
billion ringgit (about 1.326 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals increased to 92.263 million shares worth
694.229 million ringgit (about 277.692 million US dollars) from
64.170 million shares valued at 429.630 million ringgit (about
171.852 million US dollars) previously.  
</P>
