<HEADLINE> OECD Forecasts Portugal's GDP Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Portugal's gross domestic product
(GDP) would grow by 2.25 percent this year, and 2.75 percent next
year, according to the latest survey of the Organization for
Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD).
</P>
<P>
The survey said that the Portuguese government has made great
progress in the economic macro-control, which led to the drop of
inflation rate, the falling of bank interests rate and the
decrease of the budgetary deficit.
</P>
<P>
Portugal's huge public debt still posed as a major problem,
accounting for over 70 percent of the country's GDP, the OECD said.
</P>
<P>
The Paris-based organization suggested that Portugal reform the
management over the debt, take concrete measures to reduce the
public expending and crack down economic crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
