<HEADLINE> Exporters in Thailand to Be Exempted from Income Tax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government's Board of
Investment (BOI) has agreed to grant more privileges to
export-oriented projects which ship at least 80 percent of their
products abroad.
</P>
<P>
These projects, classified as the sixth type of special
businesses, will enjoy income tax exemptions for eight years and
100 percent machinery tax exemptions, according to local newspaper
the Nation today.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the BOI gives special privileges to five types of
projects -- transport infrastructure, utilities, environmental
protection and restoration, technology development and basic
industries.
</P>
<P>
The decision came after Thai exports in the first six months
grew only 7.1 percent compared to more than 20 percent in the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The BOI will shortly seek cabinet approval for these special
privileges to be granted to export-oriented projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
