<HEADLINE> All S. Koreans Confirmed Dead in Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 10 (Xinhua) -- All seven people aboard the rescue
helicopter which crashed at the foot of the Chiri Mountain in
South Korea's South Kyongsang Province last night were confirmed
dead, said reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated copter crashed in bad weather deep in the remote
mountain area of the southern part of the country after rescuing
two university student climbers, according to the reports.
</P>
<P>
Police found the dead crew and passengers among the copter
wreck this morning near a temple some 1.5 kilometers from a
mountain retreat in Sanchong County of the province, the place
where the helicopter picked up the two mountain climbers, one of
them suffering from backpain.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter from a fire station flew to the mountain villa
last night when the mountain climbers called for help.
</P>
<P>
However, communication was cut off between the copter and the
fire station soon after the helicopter took off, the reports
quoted the police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The police attribute the crash to heavy rains and the ensuing
thick fog which blanketed the Chiri Mountain yesterday evening.
</P>
</TEXT>
