<HEADLINE> Hubei to Export More Machinery, Electronic Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Hubei Province in central China
plans to export an annual one billion US dollars worth of
machinery and electronic products by the end of this century.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial planning commission said that
the province will upgrade machinery and electronic products with a
focus on motor vehicles and parts, motorcycles, video and
electronic medical equipment, and digital control machine tools.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it will spend more on developing new machinery and
electric products and encourage banks to support the
export-oriented machinery and electronic enterprises.
</P>
<P>
While approving more enterprises with better economic
performance to export their products, the provincial government
will support foreign-funded machinery and electronic enterprises
in the fields of energy, transport and loans.
</P>
<P>
One of China's old industrial bases, Hubei exported 350 million
US dollars worth of machinery and electronic products last year.
</P>
