<HEADLINE> Market Indicators in Dhaka Stock Exchange Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The market capitalization of the DSE fell by tk 1.2793 billion
(about 31.98 million US dollars) to tk 77.3114 billion (about
1.932 billion dollars) from tk 78.5907 billion (about 1.964
billion dollars) in the previous week.
</P>
<P>
On an average 550,000 shares and debentures valued at more than
tk 110 million (2.75 million dollars) changed hands daily during
the last week against the previous week's 587,000 shares worth
more than tk 120 million (3 million dollars), a DSE official
confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Market operation and share brokers said that the market
indicators went down because a selling pressure dominated the DSE
floor during the week. Despite the liberal policy measures
proposed in the 1996-1997 budget, foreign investors are still
selling out their shares.
</P>
<P>
The trend was a seasonal phenomenon, DSE Chairman Imtiaz
Hossain said, adding that the market would be stable within a few
weeks.  
