<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Peru Rises to 5.7 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Peru reached
5.678 billion U.S. dollars by the end of July, said the National
Commission for Foreign Investment and Technologies (Conite) today.
</P>
<P>
Spain, the United Kingdom, and the United States are the
biggest investors, accounting for 72.2 percent of the total
foreign capital inflow.
</P>
<P>
Spain represents about 40 percent of the foreign investment in
the communications and financing sectors with nearly 2.29 billion
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
