<HEADLINE> Mexican Police Seize Drugs in Planes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Mexican police seized large
packages of drugs hidden in two light planes today, the
Attorney-General's Office said.
</P>
<P>
The first plane was found burning on a clandestine airstrip in
the southeastern state of Michoacan.
</P>
<P>
Police put out the fire that had destroyed much of the aircraft
and found 720 kilograms of marijuana in 40 packages inside.
</P>
<P>
The second plane was found and confiscated at the Hermosillo
International Airport in the northern state of Sonora during a
surveillance tour of the installations of the air terminal.
</P>
<P>
The plane was hidden in a hangar in the general aviation area
and marijuana residues were found in the cabin.
</P>
<P>
No detentions were made in either case. Judicial Police are
trying to find the pilots of both aircraft and any other people
connected with the cases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
