<HEADLINE> Indian PM's Visit to Nepal Canceled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister H.D.
Deve Gowda has canceled his visit plan to Nepal, earlier scheduled
for next month, a local newspaper said today.
</P>
<P>
Gowda canceled his visit due to the death of his mother on
Monday, the English-language daily Everest herald quoted a source
from the Nepali Foreign Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the cancellation of the Indian premier's Nepal visit
would not affect Nepali Foreign Minister Prakash Chandra Lohani's
visit to India from the coming Monday, the source said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that one major purpose of Lohani's visit
to India is to make preparations for Gowda's Nepal visit.
</P>
