<HEADLINE> Brazil Announces Investment Plan for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Cardoso today announced the country's investment plan for 1998.
</P>
<P>
The plan aims at creating "conditions for a bigger growth, a
bigger number of jobs, and an extension of the government's social
programs."
</P>
<P>
The plan envisages about 50 infrastructure projects and reduces
the autonomy of government ministries in deciding budget
expenditures.
</P>
<P>
Priority projects will be included in each ministry's budget,
and the resources needed for their implementation will not be
allowed to be used for other purposes.
</P>
<P>
These projects will cost a total of 19 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
