<HEADLINE> Myanmar Praises Thailand's Role in Airport Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Lieut. Gen. Khin
Nyunt praised Thailand's cooperation in the project of Mandalay
international airport here, the official New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the State Law and Order
Restoration Council, Friday attended the foundation-laying
ceremony of the airport, whose terminal building will be
constructed by the Italian-Thai Development Public Company.
</P>
<P>
The new airport, located in Mandalay division in the north of
the country, was initiated in March 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Italian-Thai Development Public Company will construct the
modern four-storied terminal building in three years at a cost of
about 149 million U.S. dollars and with loans from the Thai
Export-Import Bank.
</P>
<P>
Canada's Marshall Macklin Managhan Company will undertake
drawing of the master plan and design of the airport building and
will build the runway.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Pacific Consultant International will serve as the
representative of the airport building to meet the required
standards.  
</P>
</TEXT>
