<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Likely Killed in Helicopter Crash in South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Seven people on board a rescue
helicopter are feared dead after it crashed last night at the foot
of the Chiri Mountain in South Korea's South Kyongsang Province,
according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Police found the wreck near a temple about 1.5 kilometers from
a mountain retreat in Sanchong County of the province, the place
where the helicopter picked up two mountain climbers, one of them
suffering from back pain, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers were sent to the scene but they could not find
any survivors from the scattered remains of the helicopter until
this morning.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter flew from a fire station to the mountain villa
last night when the mountain climbers called for help.
</P>
<P>
However, communications were cut off between the helicopter and
the fire station soon after it took off, the reports quoted the
police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The police attributed the crash to heavy rains and the ensuing
thick fog which blanketed the Chiri Mountain yesterday evening.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
