<HEADLINE> Thailand to Impose Surcharge on Imported Steel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is likely to impose a
surcharge on imported steel products to block an influx cheep
steel imports, according to local newspaper Bangkok Post today.
</P>
<P>
The Board of Investment (BOI) of the Thai government was quoted
as saying that the BOI wanted to help domestic manufacturers of
shaped steel, cold rolled stainless steel and wire rods.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, steel manufacturers called for the BOI to impose a 30
percent surcharge on imported steel products that have seriously
hurt the local steel industry.
</P>
<P>
A surcharge is now imposed on steel similar to that of Thainox
Steel Co which produces stainless steel.  
</P>
</TEXT>
