<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand, Japan Sign Textile Technology Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial Promotion
Department (IPD) of the Thai government has signed an agreement
with the Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA) for a
program to enhance testing technology for textile and clothing
products.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper the Nation quoted today a statement issued by
IPD as saying that under the agreement that was signed on
Wednesday, JICA will help the IPD improve its textile and clothing
laboratory to meet international standards by providing modern
equipment for testing the products.
</P>
<P>
JICA will also support personnel development in the IPD's
textile industry division, including organizing an additional 10
training courses for the division's staff during 1997-2000,
sending two experts in physical and chemical testing on a long
term basis, and giving grants to documentaries and textbooks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
