<HEADLINE> 13 Killed in Truck-Train Collision in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen people were killed
and several injured when a truck was hit by a passenger train at
an unmanned level crossing in India's Andhra Pradesh Friday
evening, the National Herald reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated truck was carrying laborers of nearby cotton
ginning mills, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
