<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Union Grants Aid to Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) today
granted 500,000 U.S. dollars in aid to Costa Rica to remedy flood
damage in the southern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
EU Ambassador to Costa Rica Dieter Konig delivered the aid to
the Costa Rican National Emergency Commission. Konig said that he
had flown over the Perez Zeledon area on the Pacific coast and
witnessed the destruction done by the floods triggered by
hurricane Cesar that hit Central America on July 28 and 29.
</P>
<P>
The hurricane killed at least 40 people and destroyed roads,
bridges, houses, hospitals and water mains. In the flood-stricken
area, many roads are still closed to traffic.
</P>
<P>
Konig said the EU is planning to establish a regional emergency
program to help the reconstruction of infrastructure and housing
in Costa Rica and Nicaragua. 
</P>
</TEXT>
