<HEADLINE> Beijing University Students Conquer Mt. Anyemaqen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 10 (Xinhua/OANA) -- Five students from China's
Beijing University conquered 6,282-meter Anyemaqen Mountain in
northwest Qinghai province on August 1, the province's
mountaineering body said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Mountaineering Association said the students fought off
rainy weathers to conquer the main peak, which is located about
300 kilometers southwest to the provincial capital Xining.
</P>
<P>
One day later, three students from Qinghua University, also
based in Beijing, scaled the mountain as well.
</P>
<P>
The mountain, known for its treacherous terrains and
unpredictable weather, had been shrouded in mystery after two
Beijing college students perished in a snow storm during their
assault in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
