<HEADLINE> Bulgaria to Build First Ecological Garbage Treatment Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria will build its first
ecological garbage treatment plant in the north with the aid from
Denmark.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian Telegraph Agency (BTA) reported today that the
plant, to be built near the city of Sumen, will be able to produce
thermal energy by incinerating garbage.
</P>
<P>
The international environmental protection organization will
provide 35,000 ECU (about 44,100 U.S. dollars) for the
construction of the plant.
</P>
<P>
Denmark will send environmental experts in September to
supervise the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
