<HEADLINE> Marseille Beats Lyon in Season's Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Marseille beat the visiting Lyon
3-1 on home turf in the first match of the Serie A soccer of the
1996-1997 season on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Marseille, who suffered a relegation at the end of 1993 for
involving a corruption case, was promoted back to the Serie A this
season.
</P>
<P>
A total of 20 teams participated in Serie A competition, which
was based on a home-and-away format.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rule, there will be 18 teams in the 1997-1998
season, with the last four teams in Serie A relegated and the top
two finishers in Serie B automatically winning the promotion.
</P>
</TEXT>
