<HEADLINE> Malaysian Firm to Set up Joint Venture in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The state-run Myanmar Timber
Enterprise (MTE) and Malaysia's Kol Industries will set up a
wood-based joint venture in Yangon, the capital of Myanmar, the
official New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The MTE signed the contract with the Kol Industries here
Friday, its first with a private Malaysian firm, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, to be located in Shwepyitha Industrial Zone,
will trade in finished timber products.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Malaysia's investment in
Myanmar amounted to 312 million U.S. dollars in 10 projects as of
the end of May this year, ranking the sixth among foreign
investments in the country.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar authorities have announced that Chairman of the State
Law and Order Restoration Council senior general Than Shwe and his
wife will pay a state visit to Malaysia in the near future.
</P>
</TEXT>
