<HEADLINE> Liaoning Uses More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
province set a record in using overseas investment in the first
half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The province approved 1,202 overseas-funded enterprises in the
first six months of this year, an increase of 41.7 percent over
the same period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
They involved a total investment of 6.02 billion US dollars, of
which 3.47 billion US dollars were contractual foreign funds, up
208.7 percent, and 193.9 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning has so far approved 14,647 overseas-funded enterprises
with a total investment of 37.6 billion US dollars, of which 19.71
billion US dollars were overseas capital.
</P>
</TEXT>
