<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Hold Exhibition in Beijing to Spur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will try to induce a
greater flow of exports to the People's Republic of China by
holding an 'Indonesia Opportunities '96' exhibition in Beijing
September 26-30, 1996, a spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"The exhibition will be an answer to the challenge being faced
by Indonesia in boosting its exports to China," Susila Budi
Moeffreni, president director of Pt Indo Asean Persada, which is
organizing the event, said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition was to be organized in cooperation with the
office of Indonesia's coordinating minister for production and
distribution and China's Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Relations. It was expected to be attended by 23 companies,
including the national aircraft maker Iptn, Sahid group and Citra
Lamtoro group.
</P>
<P>
He said that Indonesia businessmen had so far been relying too
much on traditional markets while China with a population of 1.2
billion had remained a potential but untouched market.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation between China and Indonesia had expanded
rapidly since the resumption of diplomatic ties in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Direct trade between the two countries in 1989 only reached 890
million US dollars. But last year their direct bilateral trade
was recorded at 3.5 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The value of Sino-Indonesian export-import in the year 2000 was
expected to reach 400 billion US dollars, official sources said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
