<DOCNO> XIE19960810.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's GNP up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's gross national
product (GNP) reached 22.983 billion yuan in July this year, an
increase of 10.5 percent over the same period of last year, the
Shanghai Municipal Statistical Bureau reported.
</P>
<P>
Its gross domestic product (GDP) in the first seven months of
this year was 155.143 billion yuan, up 11.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's industrial output value totalled 41.096 billion yuan
in July, up 15.7 percent over the same month of last year. The
output value of heavy industry amounted to 22.741 billion yuan, an
increase of 18.2 percent, and that of light industry totalled
18.355 billion yuan, up 12.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The sales rate of industrial products in July went up to 97.8
percent, indicating that Shanghai has achieved initial results in
developing industrial market.
</P>
<P>
This China's largest economic center put 11.081 billion yuan
in fixed assets in July, an increase of 20.3 percent over the same
period of last year, and its investment in this field in the
January-July period climbed to 64.453 billion yuan, up 41.9
percent over the same 1995 period.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's consumer goods market is brisk with retail sales
volume reaching 9.321 billion yuan last month, an increase of 13.3
percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The city exported 1.179 billion US dollars worth of goods in
July, up 22.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the bureau, Shanghai still faces unfavorable
conditions in economic development such as lower efficiency of
micro-economy and weaker competence of its commodities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
