<HEADLINE> Seles Advances to Semi-finals in Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles rebounded from her
Olympic loss to move into the semi-finals of the Canadian Open
women's tennis tournament on Friday with a straight sets victory
over Bulgarian Magdalena Maleeva in Montreal on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The world co-number one and top-seeded American downed
sixth-seeded Maleeva 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Seles will now play unseeded Indonesian Yayuk Basuki in
Saturday's semi-finals after Basuki, ranked 31st in the world,
stunned 13th-seeded American Amy Frazier 2-6, 6-2, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
In the other two quarter-finals, fifth-seeded American Mary Joe
Fernandez fell to compatriot Kimberly Po 6-2, 6-3, and
second-seeded Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain ousted Florencia
Labat of Argentina 6-4, 6-4 as expected. 
</P>
