<HEADLINE> World Youth Baseball Championship Opens in Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 9 (Xinhua/OANA) -- China beat Mexico 10-7 in
Group B on the opening day of the World Youth Baseball
Championship here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that China competed in a International
Baseball Federation Class AAA tournament. But it would not be
listed on the final standings as nine of its players are over 18
years old.
</P>
<P>
Also in the group, Chinese Taipei overpowered Nicaragua 12-2.
The other teams in the group are the Netherlands and host Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The group A comprises Brazil, South Korea, Italy, Panama, the
United States and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The top two teams in each group advance into the semi-final on
August 15 and the final is slated on August 16. 
