<HEADLINE> Water Shortage Hits Indonesia's Central Java </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- A severe draught is prevailing
in Indonesia's Central Java province, affecting more than one
million people in 773 villages, said reports reaching here today
from Semarang, capital of the province.
</P>
<P>
Hartono, a senior provincial official, said Friday that the
draught hit 13,203 hectares of paddy fields and 925 hectares of
second-crop fields.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6,636 hectares of paddy fields have been completely
destroyed, he said.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that several dams in the province dried up and
cited the example of the huge Kedungombo dam, where farmers could
plant second crops on parts of the exposed bottom of the dam's
artificial lake.  
</P>
