<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourism In Central Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The city of Wuhan, capital of Hubei
Province, has plans to promote local tourism in the next five
years, to make it one of the best tourist cities in China.
</P>
<P>
Located on the middle reaches of the Yangtze River, the city is
rich in tourism resources, with seven forest parks in the suburbs,
dozens of natural scenic spots or sites of historical and cultural
significance, and numerous lakes and hills around the city.
</P>
<P>
More than 624,000 tourists visited Wuhan over the past five
years, increasing on average 9.72 percent each year.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan plans to expand and improve its scenic zones, and open
its first tourist farm. It will also build ten large tourist
projects, including a zoo for both visiting and hunting, a sea
animal park, a theme park of cultures around the world, and a golf
course.
</P>
<P>
The city has made progress in improving its tourist facilities,
and has 30 factories making souvenirs, 65 travel services, and
more than 30 hotels.
</P>
<P>
A total of 62 domestic and international air routes have been
opened from the city's Tianhe Airport, and a new railway station
in Hankou has just been completed and service will start at a new
passenger port.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
